Report/getpatientallpriorsreports.reportContent:
RADIOGRAPHS OF THE LEFT FOOT

CLINICAL HISTORY: Left foot pain, arthritis

TECHNIQUE: Two views of the LEFT foot were obtained.

COMPARISON: None.

FINDINGS: The bones are osteopenic. There is no fracture. The middle phalanx of the fourth toe is absent. There is normal alignment. There is a plantar calcaneal spur measuring 8 mm. The articular surfaces and spaces are preserved. There are no obvious blastic or lytic lesions. There is no evidence of significant soft tissue swelling.There are multiple calcified atherosclerotic plaques.

IMPRESSION:

Absent medial phalanx of the fourth toe
Plantar calcaneal spur.
Calcified atherosclerotic plaques suggesting diabetes.
Osteopenia.


------
Signed by Alex Bugnone - 11/10/2023 07:52:57 PM (EST)
------
